author: Reuters Editorial
title: BRIEF-Raymond James Financial Says ‍Total Securities Commissions And Fees In Jan 2018, Increased 13% Over Jan 2017 ​
text:
Feb 21 (Reuters) - Raymond James Financial Inc:
* RAYMOND JAMES FINANCIAL INC - ‍TOTAL SECURITIES COMMISSIONS AND FEES OF $379 MILLION IN JAN 2018, INCREASED 13% OVER JAN 2017 AND 2% OVER DEC 2017​
* RAYMOND JAMES FINANCIAL INC - CLIENT ASSETS UNDER ADMINISTRATION OF $750.2 BILLION AT JAN END, INCREASED 21% COMPARED TO JANUARY 2017
* RAYMOND JAMES FINANCIAL INC - ‍RECORD FINANCIAL ASSETS UNDER MANAGEMENT OF $134.9 BILLION IN JAN , AN INCREASE 66% OVER JANUARY 2017​
* RAYMOND JAMES FINANCIAL INC - ‍RECORD NET LOANS AT RAYMOND JAMES BANK OF $18.0 BILLION IN JAN, UP 13% OVER JAN 2017​ Source text: ( bit.ly/2EIrzej ) Further company coverage:
